  "prompt": "In a tube with a cons. H2O pres. of 2bar are located on a horizontal piece 3nozzles with different diamtrs.From what gland splashing water thehighest?",
  "response": "Let's solve this step by step:\n\n1) First, recall the principle of water flow from an opening:\n\u2022 The water flow velocity depends on the pressure and the nozzle diameter\n\u2022 The flow velocity is determined by the equation: v = \u221a(2gh)\n\n2) In this case, h represents the pressure head\n\u2022 Pressure is given as 2 bar\n\u2022 1 bar = 10 meters of water column\n\n3) So, h = 2 \u00d7 10 = 20 meters\n\n4) The flow velocity will be: v = \u221a(2 \u00d7 9.81 \u00d7 20)\n\u2022 9.81 is acceleration due to gravity\n\u2022 v = \u221a(392.4)\n\u2022 v \u2248 19.81 m/s\n\n5) The actual water jet height depends on the nozzle's cross-sectional area\n\u2022 The smallest diameter nozzle will have the highest water jet height\n\u2022 This is because the velocity is concentrated in a smaller area\n\n6) Therefore, water will splash the HIGHEST from the SMALLEST diameter nozzle.\n\nThe answer: From the smallest diameter nozzle.",
